be doing similar work.

00:32:04.430 --> 00:32:07.890
One tricky thing with
revitalization overall is

00:32:07.890 --> 00:32:10.420
that there's no one-size-fits-all.

00:32:10.420 --> 00:32:13.410
And what works with one
community might totally bomb

00:32:13.410 --> 00:32:14.890
in another community.

00:32:14.890 --> 00:32:22.200
So, Breath of Life is a very
effective way for the experience

00:32:22.200 --> 00:32:25.710
of people doing revitalization
in language reclamation.

00:32:25.710 --> 00:32:28.730
So, in the cases where there
are no longer speakers,

00:32:28.730 --> 00:32:33.700
or the base of first language
speakers was lost at some point.

00:32:33.700 --> 00:32:37.180
And share those experiences
so that other practitioners

00:32:37.180 --> 00:32:44.180
of revitalization can adapt those
experiences to their own benefit.

00:32:44.180 --> 00:32:48.870
National Breath of Life, actually
one of the main objectives

00:32:48.870 --> 00:32:53.650
of the program is to allow
participants to become part

00:32:53.650 --> 00:32:57.360
of a growing network of
revitalization practitioners.

00:32:57.360 --> 00:33:00.480
That's one of those things that
are a little bit intangible.

00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:02.790
It's difficult to measure.

00:33:02.790 --> 00:33:08.140
But we know that over time, all of
these practitioners will be talking

00:33:08.140 --> 00:33:10.760
